    "original_title": "Manhattan: 14th Street (East) - Broadway",
    "text": "East 14th Street, south side, at Broadway, as photographed southwestward from Union Square East (4th Ave.) and 15th Street.  The ornate building at the S.W. corner was demolished and replaced with a modern office structure.  Adjoining same is the women's finishing house of Orbachs.  It remains after absorption of the adjacent building occupied by Abels.  Note the equestrian Washington statue at the left.  This was removed to a new site inside of the park.\nJanuary 30, 1928\nP.L. Sperr\n",
    "text_source": "site",
